River City Ransom was my all-time favorite NES game (sorry, #supermariobros3 ), and this is an incredible follow-up. Also rolls Double Dragon into the fold (won’t spoil how). If you’re lookin for a good  old-school beat-em up with some rpg-type elements, you’ll love this. #rivercitygirls #misako #kyoko #rivercityransom #doubledragon #nintendo #nintendoswitch #beatemup #retrogaming

caption.text:
Seven days of #kookievision, based on my latest Link's Awakening sugar cookie set. Day four. Chain Chomp. Yes, he's a Mario character, but here's a fun fact: did you know that he was originally created as a Zelda enemy? He makes an appearance in a few of the Legend of Zelda games, actually. In Link's Awakening, Madam MeowMeow of Mabe Village has a pet Chain Chomp in her front yard named BowWow. Link's Awakening is full of odes to Mario - not just this guy!

If you want to see more, I created a 20 minute video compilation of the entire set. No instructions, no dialogue, just some music. Check out "Kookievision" on the Sweethart Baking Experiment YouTube channel to watch it.

For my favourite sugar cookie dough and royal icing recipe, visit the "How To" section of my website at sweethartbaking.com.

Do you love my cookie videos and want to see more? Check me out on Ko-Fi to make a small coffee-sized Paypal donation towards the future of Kookievision:
☕ ko-fi.com/sweethart

Music is "Powerup!" by Jeremy Blake from the YouTube audio library.

caption.text:
He’s a...
Credit to TaitherZ on Twitter

Astral Chain has got me ⛓CHAINED⛓ up lately. 😂
-
The next game out of Platinum Games, the studio behind Bayonetta, is back with another game that is uniquely and evidently another Platinum Games creation, with its graphical style and excellent gameplay. 🎮
-
I was not expecting to enjoy this game as much as I am. Controlling two characters at the same time is a bit tricky at first, but with enough practice, it becomes so fluid and really amps up the action. 👊🏻
-
Have you picked up Astral Chain yet? If you’re on the fence about it, fear not - you will LOVE it. 👍🏻

Okay, so my SNES's power supply is failing. The common failure of retro tech is the power supply starts to go bad, and starts outputting higher voltage than normal, frying the rest of the system along with it. But I was suspecting this was happening, because the console has been acting weird lately. On Lemmings, the controller d-pad was having inverted input (I press left it goes right, up goes down, etc.) And the final clue happened recently, in SMW. When I would complete a level, the game would crash when the spotlight would normally fade out on Mario. I think this was God saying "hey, better stop and check the voltage on that power supply, you pizza". Thank God I checked, cause it was outputting 13 volts. I checked again before posting, now it's almost 14, so it's confirmed. I think the console and game is fine, I just need a new power supply. If you read all this, comment SNES to show your support! I'll give you updates when I get a new power supply.

.
Purchased Today: 8bitdo SN30 Pro+
Platform: Nintendo Switch
——-
I decided it was time to get myself a controller that has a good Dpad and it’s comfortable to use. Youtubers and other influencers have been singing the praises of the 8bitdo SN30 Pro+, and after trying it out for a night, I have to agree. Nintendo’s pro controller, as good as it is, has a dpad that is prone to phantom inputs and incorrect inputs by its very construction. The 8bitdo controller doesn’t have that issue, and is compatible with Windows, Mac, Android, Steam, and the Switch. You can configure the controller using 8bitdo’s software to change button mappings, stick and trigger sensitivity, add macros, change vibration strength, and more. It really is a versatile controller, and considering it’s only $50, it’s a better deal than the pro controller. The only downside is that it can’t wake up the switch using the home button like the pro controller can.
——-

✨Gamer Soul✨
En mi casa nunca hubo una consola cuando era niña, ni siquiera tenía televisión por cable, lo más cercano que tuve a algo donde jugar fue mi pc con emuladores que descargue junto con 5 virus de ares 😂😂😂
Hace un par de año conseguimos un PS4 pero aún así es compartido con mi hermanos.
Hace 3 días, después de un año de trabajo, compre mi switch lite. Y puedo decir con gusto que es mía.
Se que podrá no ser tan importante pero conseguir algo que deseabas con tu propio esfuerzo.
Gracias a todos los que llegaron hasta aquí ❤️ luche por lo que quieren

caption.text:
”Final Fantasy VII establishes A New Standard Of Excellence For PlayStation Games” And This Headline Still Stands Strong Today In 2019 - This Is A Rare And Original Final Fantasy VII Midgar EU Exclusive “Not For Sale” Promo Postcard ; Promoting It’s November 14th Release In 1997 In Europe With It’s Original Price of £44.99
.
One of my personal and original favourites ofc for the Midgar art but also I love the back of the Card itself as it has some very interesting info which talks about FFVII and it’s phenomenal success in Japan and US alongside some mini reviews and scores for the game where PlayStation gave it a 10/10 aswell as it’s original price of £44.99 , I specifically love the quote they used about the game having 3 discs and saying “ That will take a lifetime to complete” cause then FFVIII and FFIX then went onto have 4 discs each i just find that so retro and funny how they highlighted that in particular before the days of DVD discs 👌🏻
.
This postcard was only obtained through Promotional Purposes Prior to its EU Release and couldn’t be bought, they seem to be very rare nowadays would look great framed . #game #games #gamer #gaming #gamers #videogames #finalfantasy #kingdomhearts #squareenix #ps4 #playstation #ps1 #finalfantasy7 #ffvii #picoftheday #pictureoftheday #nintendo #xbox #cloudstrife #jrpg #retro #anime #japan #nintendoswitch #rpg #art #ff7remake #finalfantasycollection #finalfantasyvii #playstation4

Já que o Remake de Final Fantasy VII esta cada mais perto, hoje eu quero lembrar o título que encerra o arco dessa história fantástica. Dirge of Cerberus: Final Fantasy VII saiu para PS2 em 2006 e foi algo bem arriscado feito pela Square Enix. O jogo é um shooter em terceira pessoa e traz Vincent Valentine como protagonista contra uma organização que até então não aparecia nos títulos anteriores, porém tem uma visão parecida com o que a Shinra fazia. Dirge of Cerberus não é o melhor jogo da série e seu gameplay pode ter sido um dos principais motivos de tantas críticas, mas sua história é interessante e ver todos os personagens juntos novamente é algo muito legal. Particularmente eu gosto do jogo e suas mecânicas não são tão ruins assim, mas entendo quem critica. Gostaria muito que uma versão HD saísse para os consoles atuais, mas aí eu to sonhando muito grande.
